<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-07-31T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-07-31T16:00:00-05:00" n="652" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d652">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.706/161: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in China (<persName type="to">Johnson</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-07-31T17:00:00-04:00">July 31, 1933—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>270. Your 627, July 27, 11 a.m., last paragraph. In the light of Peck’s
                            and your views that extension of informal good offices would be
                            appropriate and useful, Department authorizes you in your discretion to
                            proceed as indicated.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>